<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<subsection xml:id="homework" component="homework">
  <title>Homework</title>
  <p>
    Homework assignments are a critical component of the course.
    They are designed to reinforce the concepts covered in the text and provide hands-on experience.
    Collaboration is encouraged, but each student must submit their own work.
  </p>
  
  <p>
    Homework will be completed using ALEKS. All assignments are available at the beginning of the course.
    The problems are chosen to highlight the core concepts from the material.
    Mastery of these homework sets serves as a good indicator for performance on assessments.
    As such, you should ensure that you fully understand the material on these homework sets; that is, upon completion of the homework set, you should be capable of completing similar problems without the aid of the text, a computer, or any other tools not available during an exam.
  </p>
</subsection>
